{
    "Description": "<p> 🔄  <strong>Replacement:</strong> <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240); color: rgb(37, 144, 205);\"><a href=\"@os.platform\" target=\"_blank\">os.platform</a></code>. </p><p> ⚠️  <strong>Deprecated:</strong>    <code style=\"background-color: rgb(240, 240, 240);\">os.whichOs</code> will be removed in a future version.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">os.whichOs()\n</pre><p><br></p><h3>Notes</h3><ul><li>Returns the name of the host operating system.</li><li>Valid return values include:</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>\"macOS\"</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>\"Windows\"</code></li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\"><code>\"Linux\"</code></li><li><strong>Deprecated</strong>: This function will be removed in a future version. Use <code>os.platform</code> for forward compatibility.</li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">local OS = os.whichOs()\ntrace(OS)&nbsp; -- \"macOS\", \"Windows\", or \"Linux\"\n</pre>",
    "Name": "os.whichOs",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "*DEPRECATED* - Use os.platform instead."
}